  "prompt": "How did Harry's get its name?",
  "response": "Harry's, the well-known brand of men's grooming products, was founded by Harry's co-founders Jeff Raider and Andy Katz-Mayfield. The name \"Harry's\" was chosen to evoke a sense of simplicity, approachability, and reliability, reflecting the brand's mission to provide quality grooming products at an affordable price. The name itself personifies the idea of a friend or trusted source for personal care, aligning with their vision to create a more pleasant shaving experience and to disrupt the traditional razor market, which was often characterized by high prices and limited choices. The choice of a common first name helps to create a relatable and friendly image for the brand.",
